They were among the first creatures to invade the land during one of the great evolutionary transitions in Earth's history.

Now, scientists believe the first four-limbed vertebrates, known as tetrapods, that lived 360 million years ago may have been more like modern crocodiles than previously thought.

They were able to reconstruct the skull of one of these animals in 3D from fragments of fossils that have been found in East Greenland.

